HEADWORD: Nomad
<hw>Nom"ad</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>nomas</ets>,
<ets>-adis</ets>, Gr. <?/, <?/, pasturing, roaming without fixed home,
fr. <?/ a pasture, allotted abode, fr. <?/ to distribute, allot, drive
to pasture; prob. akin to AS. <ets>niman</ets> to take, and E.
<ets>nimble</ets>: cf. F. <ets>nomade</ets>. Cf. <er>Astronomy</er>,
<er>Economy</er>, <er>Nimble</er>, <er>Nemesis</er>, <er>Numb</er>,
<er>Number</er>.]</ety> <def>One of a race or tribe that has no fixed
location, but wanders from place to place in search of pasture or
game.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nomad</ent>⟦br⟧

